Fifty children were infected with HRV: 22 as a single infection and 28 as co-infection with RSV. We could typify 21/50 strains of HRV (42%); 13 outpatients and 8 hospitalized infants (Fig. 1
). Seven strains belong to genogroup A, seven to the genogroup B and seven to genogroup C. There were no differences among genogroups of HRV, as a single infection or as co-infection whit RSV (p
 = 0.8), neither according to severity of illness.
